using (SqlCommand CodeStatus = new SqlCommand(SQL, DB))\n{\n    DB.Open();\n    SqlDataAdapter adapter = new SqlDataAdapter(CodeStatus);\n    DataTable dataTable = new DataTable();\n    adapter.Fill(dataTable);\n    \n    // Ensure the dataTable has at least one row\n    if (dataTable.Rows.Count > 0)\n    {\n        FormView1.DataSource = dataTable;\n        FormView1.DataBind();\n    }\n    else\n    {\n        // Handle no data scenario, e.g., set an empty template or message\n        FormView1.Visible = false; // Or any other handling logic\n    }\n    \n    DB.Close();\n}